PRACTICAL2.3 : Drawable & Dimension Resources (TCSC) 
STEP 1: Open Android Studio 
      • Click New Project 
      
STEP 2: Select Project Template 
      • Choose Empty Views Activity 
      • Click Next 
      
STEP 3: Configure Your Project 
        Fill exactly like this: 
        Field 
        Name 
        Package name 
        Save location 
        Language 
        Minimum SDK 
        Value 
        CollegeNoticeApp 
        com.example.collegenoticeapp 
        Default 
        Java 
        API 21 (Android 5.0) 
        Build configuration language Default 
        Click Finish 
        Wait until Gradle build completes. 
        
STEP 4: Add Image (Drawable Resource) 
        1. Copy your image logo.jpg 
        2. Go to: 
        app → src → main → res → drawable 
        3. Paste logo.jpg inside drawable 
        No renaming required 
        
STEP 5: Create Dimension Resources 
        Open: 
        res → values → dimens.xml 
        If not present: 
        • Right-click values 
        • New → Values Resource File 
        • Name: dimens 
dimens.xml
          <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
          <resources> 
              <dimen name="logo_size">120dp</dimen> 
              <dimen name="padding_large">16dp</dimen> 
              <dimen name="padding_medium">12dp</dimen> 
              <dimen name="text_large">20sp</dimen> 
              <dimen name="text_medium">16sp</dimen> 
          </resources> 
          
STEP 6: Edit Layout File  

activity_main.xml     
            <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
            <LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" 
                android:layout_width="match_parent" 
                android:layout_height="match_parent" 
                android:orientation="vertical" 
                android:gravity="center" 
                android:padding="@dimen/padding_large"> 
             
                <ImageView 
                    android:layout_width="@dimen/logo_size" 
                    android:layout_height="@dimen/logo_size" 
                    android:src="@drawable/logo" 
                    android:contentDescription="College Logo" 
                    android:layout_marginBottom="@dimen/padding_medium" /> 
             
                <TextView 
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content" 
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
                    android:text="TCSC" 
                    android:textSize="@dimen/text_large" 
                    android:layout_marginBottom="@dimen/padding_medium" /> 
             
                <TextView 
                    android:layout_width="wrap_content" 
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
                    android:text="College Notice Board" 
                    android:textSize="@dimen/text_medium" /> 
            </LinearLayout> 
            
STEP 7: Java File 
MainActivity.java    Default code is sufficient: 

package com.example.collegenoticeapp; 
import android.os.Bundle; 
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity; 
public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity { 
    @Override 
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) { 
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState); 
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main); 
    } 
} 

STEP 8: Run the Application 
1. Click Run 
